<br>
I was reading a book of Warren Ellis's dispatches and he was remarking how ugly most comics look. He also mentioned that he has boxes of cheap paperback novels which have better covers than most comics.<br>
<br>
Although that was written a few years ago, I think it's still true:There's still an awful lot of very bland cover art crowding the shelves. Sometimes I go into Forbidden Planet and it looks like the comic book version of the bayeux tapestry - a long line of comics all with very similar cover artwork - all depicting badly drawn super heroes, posing together in groups, or grappling with intergalactic menaces.<br>
<br>
Lucifer's an exception. The covers are distinctive and they look good on display. Original art is way beyond my means but if Vertigo put out a line of prints, I'd buy them. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/blucifer.showUserPublicProfile?gid=backwards7>backwards7</A> at: 10/4/03 3:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/blucifer.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mcpeckham>mcpeckham</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FFFF99>(10/5/03 9:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fluciferfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A book of Dustcovers?</span><hr size=1> I'm with you Erik.  I'd sure like to see a little more critical attention paid to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Lucifer</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, both visual and textual.  I really think Mike should have had it cinched in 2001, at least for the &quot;Best New Series&quot; award.<br>
<br>
Of course, all I was hearing about back then from the average comic buyer was <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Powers</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Promethea</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>100 Bullets</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Apparently the &quot;cool&quot; factor still weighs heavy, and for the same reasons I wouldn't call Milton or Dante or Blake &quot;cool&quot; (even in their day) I can maybe see why <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Lucifer</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> isn't stepping up to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Daredevil</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Hulk</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Fables</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Y: The Last Man</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I've read 'em all, and they're good fun, but they're no <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Lucifer</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
I've really enjoyed the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Lucifer</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> covers, especially Chris's work, which is terrific and often extraordinary. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/blucifer.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mcpeckham>mcpeckham</A> at: 10/5/03 9:35 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fluciferfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=14.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fluciferfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=14.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fluciferfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14.topic&index=2><img src=http://lightbringer.mattpeckham.com/pics/add_reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fluciferfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=14.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fluciferfrm1.threadControl?topicID=14.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/black_default/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fluciferfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=14.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fluciferfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=14.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"><